# hilavitkutin-ctx — backlog

## define_providers_generic! facade

A single-call facade mixing concrete and parameterised providers,
analogous to `define_providers!`. Nice-to-have for consumers that
declare many providers at once. Not needed until a second
multi-provider consumer surfaces that mixes the two shapes.

## Higher-arity tuple_generic! impls

`tuple_generic!` ships with enough arity to cover hilavitkutin's
WU-context needs (roughly 5-7 providers per layout). If a consumer
exceeds the shipping arity, extend the macro with additional
match arms. Purely mechanical.

## Proc-macro rewrite

The declarative macros are approaching their limits. A proc-macro
could simplify the repeated per-arity expansions and give better
error messages. Defer until either:
- the declarative arm count becomes painful to maintain, or
- a consumer surfaces an error message that's opaque enough to
  justify the proc-macro compile-time cost.

## Optional `Context<P>` inherent methods

Today `Context<P>` just wraps `providers: P`. Some consumers may
want `Context::new(providers)` / `Context::into_inner()` /
`Context::as_providers(&self) -> &P` helpers. Add when a consumer
demands them; keep the wrapper minimal until then.
